# Review Source Path Discipline

- When the user provides an explicit review file path (for example a `code-review.md` under a specific folder), always treat that exact path as the source of truth.
- Before implementing fixes from a review, confirm the loaded file path matches the user-provided path.
- If multiple similarly named review files exist, explicitly disambiguate and ask before proceeding.
